{{Infobox hieroglyphs
|TITEL = Seret
|NAME = <hiero>S29-D21:t-F8 N14-N33*N33*N33:N33*N33*N33:N33*N33*N33</hiero>
|NAME-TRANSKRIPTION = Seret<br />''Sr.t''<br />''(Head) of the Sheep''
}}

'''Seret''' is the designation of an [[:en:Ancient Egypt|Ancient Egypt]] [[:en:Decan|Decan]], which comprised nine {{ill|Baktiu|1=Baktiu|2=de|3=Baktiu|de|Baktiu|1=Baktiu|2=de|3=Baktiu|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Baktiu|qq=}} (decan stars) and belonged to the Ancient Egyptian [[:en:Constellation|Constellation]] {{ill|Sheep (constellation)|de|Schaf (Sternbild)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sheep (constellation)|qq=}}, depicted in many coffins on {{ill|Diagonal star clock|de|Diagonalsternuhr|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Diagonal star clock|qq=}}s and, for example, in the tomb of [[:en:Senenmut|Senenmut]].

The most prominent [[:en:Star|Star]] in this decan is [[:en:Delta Capricorni|Deneb Algedi]] in the constellation [[:en:Capricornus|Capricornus (constellation)]].

In the decan lists of the {{ill|Book of Nut#Pharaonic period|lt=Pharaonic period|de|Nutbuch#Pharaonische Zeit|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Book of Nut#Pharaonic period|qq=}}, Seret represented the 19th decan on the body of {{ill|Nut (Egyptian mythology)|de|Nut (Ägyptische Mythologie)|1=Nut (goddess)|lt=Nut|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nut (Egyptian mythology)|13=User:Immanuelle/Nut (goddess)|qq=}}. The [[:en:Heliacal rising|Heliacal rising]] was set for the {{ill|Achet#Dating|lt=6th Achet III|de|6. Achet III|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Achet#Dating|qq=}}, based on the arrangement ordered under [[:en:Senusret III|Senusret III]] ([[:en:Twelfth Dynasty of Egypt|Twelfth Dynasty of Egypt]]) in his seventh year of reign.

== Literature ==
* [[:en:Christian Leitz|Christian Leitz]]: ''Altägyptische Sternuhren''. Peeters, Leuven 1995, ISBN 90-6831-669-9, p. 92.
* {{ill|Alexandra von Lieven|fr|Alexandra von Lieven|de|Alexandra von Lieven|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Alexandra von Lieven|qq=}}: ''Grundriss des Laufes der Sterne – Das sogenannte Nutbuch''. The Carsten Niebuhr Institute of Ancient Eastern Studies (et al.), Copenhagen 2007, ISBN 978-87-635-0406-5, pp. 62–67 and 396.

{{translated page|de|Seret (Dekan)|version=234410605|comment=Imported full de history}}

